str:Codelist.com:Name: Adjustment indicator
str:Codelist.com:Description: Adjustment indicator is a statistical technique used to remove the effects of seasonal and calendar influences operating on a data series. This codelist is based on the codelist CL_SEASONAL_ADJUST+1.0 in which the code _Z(Not applicable) was added. Extended for time transformations due to a missing transformation dimension.
